description.p:
In accordance with the invention, these objects are achieved by a process for applying a finishing paper material on a leather or fabric support material, characterized in that it comprises the steps of:
first buttering of glue on a surface of the support material;
positioning the finishing material on said support material;
ironing;
perching;
second buttering of glue, and
a finishing step.

These and other features of the present invention will become more apparent from the following detailed description of a practical embodiment thereof, disclosed by way of non-limiting example in the accompanying drawings, in which:
figure 1 shows a block diagram of the process according to the present invention;
figure 2 shows a perspective view of a sheet consisting of a leather layer finished with a paper layer, obtained by means of the process in figure 1;
figure 3 shows a vertical section view of the sheet in figure 2.

claim.claim-text:
Verfahren (100) zum Aufbringen eines abschließenden Papiermaterials (3) auf ein Leder- oder Gewebe-Trägermaterial (2),

dadurch gekennzeichnet, dass es folgende Schritte aufweist:
- erstes Aufstreichen (102) von Klebstoff (4) auf eine Oberfläche (2a) des Trägermaterials (2) ;
- Positionieren (103) des abschließenden Materials (3) auf diesem Trägermaterial (2) ;
- Bügeln (105) ;
- Stollen (107),
- zweites Aufstreichen (108) von Klebstoff (4), und
- Endbearbeitungsschritt (109).

Process (100) for applying a finishing paper material (3) on a leather or woven support material (2), characterized in that it comprises the steps of:
• first buttering (102) of glue (4) on a surface (2a) of the support material (2);
• positioning (103) of the finishing material (3) on that support material (2);
• ironing (105);
• perching (107),
• second buttering (108) of glue (4), and
• finishing step (109).

Processus (100) pour appliquer un matériau de finition à base de papier (3) sur un matériau de support en cuir ou tissé (2), caractérisé en ce qu'il comprend les étapes consistant en :
- un premier étalement (102) de colle (4) sur une surface (2a) du matériau de support (2) ;
- le positionnement (103) du matériau de finition (3) sur ce matériau de support (2) ;
- un repassage (105) ;
- un martelage (107),
- un deuxième étalement (108) de colle (4), et
- une étape de finition (109).
